36 SUMMARY
3377 This amendment makes the following changes to the bill.
38 1. It adds utilization of primary care services as a key measure that may be reported on
39 by the Maine Quality Forum as part of its annual report.
Page 2 - 132LR0919(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 981, L.D. 1497
1 2. It adds a physician specializing in obstetrics and gynecology to the definition of
2 health care practitioners that are engaged in primary care as used in the work of the Primary
3 Care Advisory Council.
4 3. It specifies that one member must represent nurse practitioners and one member
5 must represent physician assistants, adds an additional member representing health
6 insurance carriers and makes technical changes to reflect the ex officio members of the
7 Primary Care Advisory Council established in the bill.
8 4. It repeals the reporting requirements of the Maine Quality Forum and repeals the
9 laws regarding the Primary Care Advisory Council January 15, 2031.
